 speckle evolution in the context of\nforthcoming high-contrast imaging instruments, with implications for\ninstrumentation (design, observing strategies, data reduction). Such a model\ncan be used for instance to derive the timescale on which non-common path\naberrations must be sensed and corrected. We found in our data that\nquasi-static wavefront error increases with ~0.7 angstrom per minute.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 28 Feb 2013 14:47:33 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-15"}
